investment banking fees of $2.9billion
were up 6%. while advisory fees declined by
14%, reflecting depressed levels of m&a
activity, debt underwriting fees were up
2%. this 2% increase is primarily due to
growth in high yield underwriting and
structured finance fees and reflects a
partial offset of lower loan syndication
fees. the key contributor to the overall
increase in ib fees was equity underwriting
revenue, which was up 48%, reflecting
increases in market share and underwriting
volumes.
