enron-related exposure
the firms exposure to enron and enron-related entities was reduced by 11%
during the year, from $688million at december31, 2002, to $609million at
december31, 2003. the reduction was primarily due to the maturation of $50
million of debtor-in-possession financing and repayments on secured exposures.
at december31, 2003, secured exposure of $270million is performing and is
reported on an amortized cost basis.
